cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a language for describing reactive synthesis problems using temporal logic and game semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a new programming language syntax for specifying synthesis problems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed language and its translation to input for a synthesizer. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper uses formal methods to define the semantics of the language and to solve the synthesis problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of game solvers and synthesis algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in AI.
